President Donald Trump will be speaking at the Conservative Political Action Conference (CPAC) on February 24th. CPAC is an annual gathering of conservative activists where they learn from each other, receive training, and hear from prominent conservative leaders. President Trump has addressed CPAC several times in the past and will be the fourth president to do so. Vice President Mike Pence, Chief of Staff Reince Priebus, and Chief Strategist Steve Bannon have also spoken at the conference. The President's speech will be available to watch below.